1. ARCHITECTURAL DIFFERENTIATION (Host Services vs Isolation Containers)
------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Bare-Metal / Host Deployment: Installs packages directly onto the operating 
  system kernel (`apt install`). Shared libraries and direct bindings mean system 
  reconfigurations can directly trigger dependency errors or platform lockouts.
* Containerization Engine (Docker): Isolates standalone services inside independent 
  sandboxed execution processes sharing the OS layer via namespaces and cgroups, 
  guaranteeing zero cross-library contamination.

2. NGINX MULTI-PORT GATEWAY TERMINATION LOGS
--------------------------------------------
File Path Modified: /etc/nginx/sites-available/default
Configuration Ruleset:
  server {
      listen 8080 default_server;
      location / {
          proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:5000;
          proxy_set_header Host $host;
          proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
      }
  }

Verification Syntax Output:
$ sudo nginx -t
nginx: the configuration file /etc/nginx/nginx.conf syntax is ok
nginx: configuration file /etc/nginx/nginx.conf test is successful
$ sudo systemctl restart nginx

* 502 Bad Gateway State: Hit http://127.0.0.1:8080 without backend processes.
* Netcat Backend Loop Daemon Trigger:
  $ while true; do echo -e "HTTP/1.1 200 OK\r\nContent-Type: text/plain\r\n\r\n🚀 Backend App Core System Se Live Hai, Bhai!" | nc -l -p 5000; done

3. DOCKER VIRTUALIZATION INFRASTRUCTURE INSTALLATION LOGS
--------------------------------------------------------
# Step 1: Map architecture packages securely under POSIX rules
$ echo "deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/docker.gpg] https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu $(lsb_release -cs) stable" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker.list > /dev/null

# Step 2: Synchronize local apt listings and deploy core packages
$ sudo apt update && sudo apt install -y docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io

# Step 3: Verify operational status criteria
$ sudo systemctl start docker && sudo systemctl status docker
  Active: active (running) since Sat 2026-06-06 11:21:59 UTC

4. RUNNING OFFICIAL CONTAINERS & PORT REDIRECTS MAPPING
-------------------------------------------------------
# Spawning official web container using public image registries:
$ sudo docker run -d -p 9090:80 --name shubh-nginx-container nginx

Verification Active Mapping State:
$ sudo docker ps
CONTAINER ID   IMAGE   STATUS         PORTS                                   NAMES
842a3bebbdd9   nginx   Up 3 minutes   0.0.0.0:9090->80/tcp, [::]:9090->80/tcp shubh-nginx-container

Network Loopback Mapping Context:
[Windows Browser Link] ---> Strike URL http://localhost:9090
                                       │
                                       ▼
[vNIC Virtual Bridge] ----> Maps Host Port 9090 directly to Sandbox Jail Port 80
                                       │
                                       ▼
[Isolated Nginx Web Container] ----> Renders standalone pristine "Welcome to nginx!" page.

